2. Simulation¶

In [173]:
P_LIST = [0.005, 0.01, 0.03, 0.05, 0.1, 0.5, 1]
NUM_OF_SIMS = 10
start_time = data.StartTime.min()
end_time = data.EndTime.max()
total_time = end_time - start_time

def model_si_simul(starting_town_id=0, p=0.01):
    
    def is_infected(airport_id, time):
        if airport_id not in infected_airports.keys():
            return False
        else:
            return infected_airports[airport_id] < time
    
    def infect_airport(airport_id, time, p=p):
        if random.random() < p:
            if airport_id not in infected_airports.keys():
                infected_airports[airport_id] = time
            else:
                infected_airports[airport_id] = min(infected_airports[airport_id], time)
    
    infected_airports = {starting_town_id:data.StartTime.min()}
    
    for t in data.itertuples(index=False):
        if is_infected(t.Source, t.StartTime):
            infect_airport(t.Destination, t.EndTime)
                            
    return infected_airports

def mean_per_time_interval(result_dict, interval_hours=12):
    interval_secs = interval_hours * 3600
    num_of_intervals = math.ceil(total_time/interval_secs)
    
    def count_means(result_list): 
        bins = pd.Series([0] * num_of_intervals)
        for r in result_list:
            for k in r.values():
                bins[math.floor((k-start_time)/interval_secs)] += 1
        return bins.cumsum()/NUM_OF_SIMS/data.Destination.nunique()*100
    
    means = pd.DataFrame([])
    for p in sim_results.keys():
        means[''.join(['p=',str(p)])] = count_means(sim_results[p])
    
    return means

G = nx.Graph()

G.add_nodes_from(data.Source.value_counts().index)

edges = {}
for t in data.itertuples(index=False):
    s,d = t.Source,t.Destination 
    edge = (min(s,d), max(s,d))
    edges.setdefault(edge, 0)
    edges[edge] += 1
    
flights_total = len(data)
for k, v in edges.items():
    edges[k] = abs(v)/flights_total

for k, v in edges.items():
    G.add_weighted_edges_from([(k[0], k[1], v)])
